OL,3,C'It's like torture': The long battle
OL,4,Cfor adoption records access
OL,6,FIn 1964, Ms Phillips said she was
OL,7,F"taken" from her mother as a baby,
OL,8,Fsimply because she was unmarried.
OL,9,FAfter two months in foster care, she
OL,10,Fwas later adopted.
OL,12,FBetween 1949 and 1976, an estimated
OL,13,F250,000 pregnant, unmarried women and
OL,14,Fgirls were sent away to "prison-like"
OL,15,Fhomes run by the church and state and
OL,16,Fhad their babies put up for adoption.
OL,17,FOther infants died due to mistreatment
OL,18,For poor care.
OL,20,FThe legacy of that time, continues to
OL,21,Fcast a long shadow.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772110991
OL,3,C'It's like torture': The long battle
OL,4,Cfor adoption records access
OL,6,F"I was told nothing, just 'you are
OL,7,Fadopted, be grateful, your mother was
OL,8,Fyoung' and that was it," she said.
OL,10,F"That was my story for some many
OL,11,Fyears. The impact is huge, I felt like
OL,12,Fa mistake, maybe I wasn't pretty
OL,13,Fenough? I felt like there was this
OL,14,Fhuge void in me all the time."
OL,16,FOver the decades, Ms Phillips, who is
OL,17,Fa singer and musician, has searched
OL,18,Fthrough hundreds of pages of files,
OL,19,Fpouring over every last detail.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
